WEBVTT

00:06.173 --> 00:09.176
<i>[pensive instrumental music]</i>

00:09.176 --> 00:16.183
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:23.065 --> 00:26.110
<i>[woman singing in Norwegian]</i>

00:26.110 --> 00:33.117
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:45.796 --> 00:52.803
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:13.157 --> 01:16.160
<i>[whooshing]</i>

01:27.505 --> 01:29.048
[screams]

01:29.048 --> 01:30.424
[Holden] Doc!

01:34.094 --> 01:37.097
[Holden grunting]

01:38.974 --> 01:41.977
[Elvi whimpering]

01:44.730 --> 01:46.148
Are you all right?

01:48.108 --> 01:49.401
Yes.

01:50.778 --> 01:52.404
No.
No.

01:52.404 --> 01:54.365
I don't know.
I don't know.

01:54.365 --> 01:57.618
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

01:57.618 --> 01:59.036
He's gone.

01:59.036 --> 02:02.331
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:02.331 --> 02:05.459
All those big energy emitters
on the surface have stopped.

02:06.627 --> 02:09.588
Every single one of them, dead.

02:09.588 --> 02:11.257
Same with the moons.

02:11.257 --> 02:18.264
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:18.264 --> 02:20.933
I'm gonna try
the reactor again.

02:20.933 --> 02:22.768
[reactor whirs]

02:22.768 --> 02:24.645
[computer chirping]

02:24.645 --> 02:31.652
<i>♪ ♪</i>

02:33.404 --> 02:36.407
[electricity crackling]

02:41.453 --> 02:43.163
- [lights snap]
[Naomi] Yes!

02:43.163 --> 02:44.832
- We're good to go.
- Yes!

02:44.832 --> 02:46.000
[laughs]

02:46.000 --> 02:48.419
[panting]

02:48.419 --> 02:51.380
The <i>Barb's</i> reactor
is back on line.

02:51.380 --> 02:53.966
[Naomi]
The <i>Edward Israel's</i> too.

02:53.966 --> 02:56.510
<i>Edward Israel,</i>
this is the gunship <i>Rocinante.</i>

02:56.510 --> 02:58.429
I've target-locked
your drive cone.

02:58.429 --> 03:01.932
You and me are about to have
a very serious conversation.

03:01.932 --> 03:04.935
[panting softly]

03:05.936 --> 03:12.943
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:14.945 --> 03:16.363
- [gasps]
- Oh!

03:17.740 --> 03:19.158
[sighs]

03:20.117 --> 03:22.244
[Amos] Cap?

03:22.244 --> 03:23.704
How bad is it?

03:27.875 --> 03:30.002
I'm a little messed up.

03:31.086 --> 03:32.588
Let's get you outta here.

03:33.672 --> 03:39.845
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:39.845 --> 03:43.057
<i>[Felcia]</i> Rocinante,
<i>tether is free and clear.</i>

03:43.057 --> 03:45.017
<i>[Alex] Roger that,</i>
Barbapiccola.

03:45.017 --> 03:47.645
<i>Correcting orbit now.</i>

03:47.645 --> 03:50.648
[engines whooshing]

03:53.275 --> 03:56.236
- Whoo-hoo-hoo!
- We did it!

03:56.236 --> 03:57.613
<i>[man] Yes!
[Felcia] We did it!</i>

03:57.613 --> 03:58.989
<i>We saved the ore!</i>

03:58.989 --> 04:01.075
<i>[man speaking indistinctly]</i>

04:01.075 --> 04:02.451
We did it.

04:02.451 --> 04:04.787
And we will make the Inners
answer for what they did.

04:04.787 --> 04:05.788
<i>[Lucia] Yes.</i>

04:06.789 --> 04:08.999
We will all answer
for what we did.

04:29.478 --> 04:32.106
<i>[Ashford] I suppose this could
have been Marco's space.</i>

04:32.106 --> 04:33.732
This net is not old.

04:33.732 --> 04:36.276
It would have drifted away
long ago.

04:36.276 --> 04:38.946
Someone was working here
recently.

04:38.946 --> 04:41.448
[woman] Cluster was mined out
over 60 years ago.

04:41.448 --> 04:44.743
These rock just iron-nickel,
worth <i>nating nada.</i>

04:44.743 --> 04:47.579
Ah, so much for your big tip.

04:47.579 --> 04:50.082
Show me flight paths
for all ships in this vicinity

04:50.082 --> 04:51.542
in past three months.

04:52.793 --> 04:54.211
<i>[woman] Copy.</i>

04:57.798 --> 05:00.801
[indistinct chatter]

05:00.801 --> 05:02.636
Wait, wait.

05:05.097 --> 05:06.974
Yes, this ship.

05:06.974 --> 05:11.812
This one turned transponder off
approaching cluster...

05:11.812 --> 05:14.314
and back on leaving.

05:14.314 --> 05:16.817
Ah, what were you doing here?

05:20.112 --> 05:23.198
Find this ship.
Put us on course for intercept.

05:23.198 --> 05:24.241
[woman]
Yes, <i>bosmang.</i>

05:24.241 --> 05:25.534
[man screams]

05:25.534 --> 05:26.910
[clears throat]

05:26.910 --> 05:29.079
Maybe we just got another tip.

05:29.079 --> 05:30.622
[screams]

05:30.622 --> 05:33.709
[groaning, panting]

05:33.709 --> 05:36.420
- That was my favorite one.
- <i>Oso fo mi.</i>

05:36.420 --> 05:37.421
So far.

05:38.964 --> 05:40.799
- [pliers clank]
[Ashford] Get out.

05:40.799 --> 05:43.093
You heard him.

05:43.093 --> 05:45.596
- Get out!
- [exhales]

05:50.559 --> 05:52.227
He was not supposed
to do that.

05:52.227 --> 05:54.521
Guess he's not
the chain-of-command type.

05:54.521 --> 05:58.192
Well, you might as well
keep this, huh, as a souvenir.

05:58.192 --> 05:59.610
[chuckles]

06:02.905 --> 06:04.323
You intend to let me go.

06:04.323 --> 06:06.617
Well, at this point,
everything is possible.

06:06.617 --> 06:08.660
- Who can say?
- You can say.

06:08.660 --> 06:10.162
Yeah?
I can.

06:10.162 --> 06:12.331
But it depends
on what you say next.

06:12.331 --> 06:14.500
I told you what I know.

06:15.542 --> 06:17.586
You led us to some
mined-out rocks

06:17.586 --> 06:20.798
where Marco Inaros
was nowhere to be found.

06:20.798 --> 06:22.925
I told you where he was.

06:22.925 --> 06:24.802
I never said
he'd still be there.

06:24.802 --> 06:27.137
The ship Marco threw at Earth

06:27.137 --> 06:29.348
was using Martian technology.

06:29.348 --> 06:33.060
So why would Mars be helping
a Belter terrorist?

06:33.060 --> 06:34.603
I don't answer for my planet.

06:34.603 --> 06:36.105
Then you should answer
for yourself.

06:36.105 --> 06:37.856
Why were you helping him?

06:37.856 --> 06:39.233
Money.

06:39.233 --> 06:40.818
Unbelievable.

06:40.818 --> 06:42.778
A Martian naval officer,

06:42.778 --> 06:45.572
mercenary for
a vicious Belter thug.

06:45.572 --> 06:48.158
Oh, how the mighty have fallen.

06:48.158 --> 06:49.535
[scoffs]

06:49.535 --> 06:51.745
Yeah, well,
Mars ain't what it used to be.

06:51.745 --> 06:57.334
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:57.334 --> 06:59.711
Yeah, Marco feels the same.

06:59.711 --> 07:02.422
The Sohiros are brutes

07:02.422 --> 07:04.299
but dependable in their hate.

07:04.299 --> 07:06.802
They keep keen eyes and ears
on Inaros

07:06.802 --> 07:08.220
and those who help him.

07:08.220 --> 07:10.597
So we know
you were at Ceres Station.

07:10.597 --> 07:12.599
Just tell me
what you were doing there.

07:12.599 --> 07:15.352
I was on vacation.

07:15.352 --> 07:17.437
I like to gamble.

07:17.437 --> 07:19.022
The brothels are nice too.

07:19.022 --> 07:21.358
You know, Belters can be
surprisingly flexible...

07:21.358 --> 07:24.069
You are an MCRN supply officer

07:24.069 --> 07:26.488
with access to the arsenal
at Callisto.

07:26.488 --> 07:29.158
You were selling Inaros
weapons, weren't you?

07:29.158 --> 07:32.161
Well, properly applied,
anything can be a weapon.

07:32.161 --> 07:33.412
Kindness can be a weapon.

07:33.412 --> 07:39.126
<i>♪ ♪</i>

07:39.126 --> 07:41.253
Do you know
what kind of man Marco is?

07:41.253 --> 07:43.213
I'm pretty sure
I have a good idea.

07:43.213 --> 07:46.341
He's angry,
like many Belters his age,

07:46.341 --> 07:48.218
bitter about our lot in life

07:48.218 --> 07:50.554
and searching for a way
to vent his rage.

07:50.554 --> 07:51.847
He is smart.

07:51.847 --> 07:55.267
He is brave, yes, very brave,
but also very naive

07:55.267 --> 07:58.562
because he believes that
violence is the only way

07:58.562 --> 08:01.106
to get what he feels
is his due.

08:01.106 --> 08:02.566
He's got a lot
of company there.

08:02.566 --> 08:05.986
Violence is indiscriminate.

08:05.986 --> 08:08.071
If you use it as a tool,

08:08.071 --> 08:11.700
it will do more
than just kill your enemies.

08:11.700 --> 08:14.494
Sometimes it will kill
the ones you love most.

08:17.289 --> 08:19.291
Now, the Rings are a chance

08:19.291 --> 08:21.084
for all of us
to start over again

08:21.084 --> 08:24.963
if we can put
our old hatreds aside.

08:24.963 --> 08:27.716
This is the time
for Inners and Belters

08:27.716 --> 08:31.511
to join hands
and, together, build.

08:31.511 --> 08:34.264
[panting]

08:34.264 --> 08:36.725
I actually agree with you.

08:36.725 --> 08:39.102
Not about
the holding hands part

08:39.102 --> 08:41.813
but the rest, in theory,

08:41.813 --> 08:44.066
definitely.

08:44.066 --> 08:46.360
I don't know where Marco is,

08:46.360 --> 08:49.029
but beating me
is not gonna change that.

08:49.029 --> 08:53.575
Or is all this talk of putting
our hate aside just talk?

08:53.575 --> 09:00.582
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:10.425 --> 09:12.970
[door clicks, whooshes]

09:18.684 --> 09:25.148
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:25.148 --> 09:29.111
[blowing]

09:29.111 --> 09:30.779
[pliers thunk]

09:30.779 --> 09:37.786
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:44.876 --> 09:47.879
<i>[indistinct announcements
over P.A. system]</i>

09:47.879 --> 09:50.882
[indistinct chatter]

09:54.177 --> 09:56.096
[Leelee] What the hell
do you think you're doing?

09:56.096 --> 09:57.639
- None of your fucking business.
[Leelee] Funny.

09:57.639 --> 09:59.099
That's exactly
what I was gonna tell you.

09:59.099 --> 10:00.892
You wanted out.
You're out.

10:00.892 --> 10:02.811
So stay out.

10:02.811 --> 10:03.979
Fuck.

10:03.979 --> 10:05.647
[Bobbie]
You were following him too.

10:05.647 --> 10:07.274
You don't trust him either.

10:09.276 --> 10:11.903
I'd happily mop the floor
with the three of you again.

10:11.903 --> 10:13.655
And when the cops come
to break it all up,

10:13.655 --> 10:15.198
we can have a nice
long conversation

10:15.198 --> 10:17.117
about all the rotten things
we've done.

10:17.117 --> 10:18.577
Sound good?

10:21.997 --> 10:24.750
How about
we compare notes instead?

10:25.959 --> 10:27.878
I couldn't find much about
Beltran in the public record...

10:27.878 --> 10:29.171
- Me neither.
- ...so I trailed him

10:29.171 --> 10:30.672
to a naval logistics office
in New Londres.

10:30.672 --> 10:33.216
- He's a desk jockey.
- What's his rank?

10:33.216 --> 10:35.010
I think he's a sergeant.

10:35.010 --> 10:36.970
The security codes
he's been supplying us with

10:36.970 --> 10:38.638
are high-level,
typically restricted

10:38.638 --> 10:40.474
to commanding officers only.

10:40.474 --> 10:41.933
They're way above
his pay grade.

10:41.933 --> 10:45.145
He's crooked.
That's why Esai hired him.

10:45.145 --> 10:47.022
Maybe he's
an intelligence officer.

10:47.022 --> 10:48.357
How did he and Esai connect?

10:48.357 --> 10:49.566
I asked Esai that.

10:49.566 --> 10:51.943
He said they met on
a joint MVPD-MCRN task force

10:51.943 --> 10:53.653
a while back
and they just hit it off.

10:53.653 --> 10:56.239
<i>[rhythmic beat
playing over radio]</i>

10:56.239 --> 10:58.408
Look, Esai knows
what he's doing.

10:58.408 --> 11:01.536
No, he wants this score so bad,
it's clouding his judgment.

11:01.536 --> 11:02.621
Think about it.

11:02.621 --> 11:04.081
Beltran waltzes in,

11:04.081 --> 11:06.124
helps us pull off
a few good operations,

11:06.124 --> 11:08.710
builds some trust, and then
brings in a big, fat score.

11:08.710 --> 11:12.547
It's low risk, lots of money.
It's way too good to be true.

11:12.547 --> 11:14.299
- You really think it's a setup?
- Yeah.

11:14.299 --> 11:16.760
But why, and why now,
after all the jobs we've pulled?

11:16.760 --> 11:18.095
I don't know.

11:18.095 --> 11:19.930
But I don't like the fact
that Esai has no idea

11:19.930 --> 11:22.182
what merchandise he's moving.

11:22.182 --> 11:23.683
You like Esai.

11:24.684 --> 11:27.270
I'm just trying to keep him
from doing anything stupid.

11:27.270 --> 11:29.564
And me too, of course.

11:29.564 --> 11:32.275
That, unfortunately,
is unavoidable.

11:32.275 --> 11:33.819
[laughs softly]

11:35.404 --> 11:38.198
[sighs]
So you gonna go through with it?

11:38.198 --> 11:39.908
It's a lot of money.

11:39.908 --> 11:44.121
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:44.121 --> 11:45.497
Are you gonna rat us out?

11:47.749 --> 11:48.917
No.

11:50.752 --> 11:52.462
Okay.

11:52.462 --> 11:53.672
Okay.

11:53.672 --> 11:59.845
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:59.845 --> 12:03.140
The customs agent
in the salvage yard,

12:03.140 --> 12:05.767
he was shaking me down
to try and renegotiate his cut.

12:05.767 --> 12:07.686
He got physical, so I did too.

12:07.686 --> 12:09.980
He took a bad tumble,
and that was it.

12:09.980 --> 12:12.607
I never meant to kill him.

12:12.607 --> 12:19.614
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:36.798 --> 12:38.800
You should probably
roll that a little tighter.

12:40.343 --> 12:41.761
Sorry.

12:45.015 --> 12:46.850
- [grunts]
- [yelps]

12:46.850 --> 12:49.227
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

12:49.227 --> 12:50.645
[Holden] Stay.

12:50.645 --> 12:56.151
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:56.151 --> 12:57.652
How you doing?

13:00.530 --> 13:02.449
I'm okay.

13:02.449 --> 13:04.534
[Elvi]
The bleeding is under control.

13:04.534 --> 13:07.120
But he's going to need regrowth
gel as soon as possible.

13:10.582 --> 13:13.126
What'd you see in there?

13:13.126 --> 13:16.129
<i>[foreboding music]</i>

13:16.129 --> 13:17.964
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:17.964 --> 13:19.966
It was more like I felt it.

13:22.802 --> 13:26.681
I know that sounds crazy, but...

13:26.681 --> 13:30.143
I could feel the spaces

13:30.143 --> 13:32.562
between things.

13:32.562 --> 13:33.980
Something was there...

13:35.774 --> 13:38.109
...a presence,

13:38.109 --> 13:40.487
moving towards me.

13:40.487 --> 13:43.365
I've felt it too,

13:43.365 --> 13:45.700
every time we go through a Ring.

13:45.700 --> 13:47.744
You're not crazy.

13:47.744 --> 13:54.751
<i>♪ ♪</i>

13:54.751 --> 13:56.336
I might rather be.

13:56.336 --> 13:59.631
We can talk more about it
when we get back to the ship.

14:01.591 --> 14:05.095
[sighs]
If we get back to the ship.

14:05.095 --> 14:07.514
I'm not sure
I'm up for a long walk...

14:09.391 --> 14:11.810
...especially if we have
to carry deadweight.

14:11.810 --> 14:17.983
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:17.983 --> 14:21.111
[Holden] That looks climbable.

14:21.111 --> 14:22.571
That looks like sky to me.

14:24.322 --> 14:26.032
Wait here.
I'll check it out.

14:26.032 --> 14:27.951
Maybe we can get a signal
up there.

14:27.951 --> 14:30.996
Oh, and, Amos,

14:30.996 --> 14:33.456
don't kill him while I'm gone.

14:34.624 --> 14:36.167
[sighs]
He has it coming.

14:36.167 --> 14:39.170
I know,
but it's important to me.

14:39.170 --> 14:40.797
Promise.

14:40.797 --> 14:47.804
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:12.495 --> 15:19.502
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:21.171 --> 15:24.174
[grunting]

15:32.807 --> 15:35.810
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

15:35.810 --> 15:42.817
<i>♪ ♪</i>

15:53.953 --> 15:55.705
<i>[Holden]</i> Rocinante.

15:55.705 --> 15:57.082
Jim?

15:57.082 --> 15:58.208
<i>[Holden] Can you hear me?</i>

15:58.208 --> 16:00.210
Yes.
Are you all right?

16:00.794 --> 16:02.170
That depends.
Are you?

16:02.170 --> 16:03.922
<i>[Naomi] We're fine, all of us.</i>

16:03.922 --> 16:06.257
Physics and fusion
are back to normal.

16:06.257 --> 16:08.760
And the reactors on all the
ships are back up and on line.

16:08.760 --> 16:10.220
<i>[Holden] Thank God.</i>

16:10.845 --> 16:13.598
I'm with Amos,
Dr. Okoye, and Murtry.

16:13.598 --> 16:15.892
We're wounded
and we need evac and...

16:15.892 --> 16:17.769
<i>I'm not sure where we are.</i>

16:17.769 --> 16:20.480
Uh...

16:20.480 --> 16:21.648
Cap, we're showing you roughly

16:21.648 --> 16:23.233
800 kilometers
from First Landing.

16:23.233 --> 16:25.151
<i>[Holden] I'm not surprised.</i>
- How the hell?

16:25.151 --> 16:26.903
<i>[Holden] It's a long story.</i>

16:27.529 --> 16:29.989
I'll tell you all about it
when you pick us up.

16:29.989 --> 16:31.408
<i>[Naomi] We're on our way.</i>

16:31.408 --> 16:38.206
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:38.206 --> 16:41.209
[thrusters whooshing]

16:45.088 --> 16:46.715
[indistinct chatter]

16:46.715 --> 16:49.384
If he know nothing more,
why waste the air?

16:49.384 --> 16:51.219
Yeah.
We make lesson <i>wit im.</i>

16:51.219 --> 16:52.637
Oh, <i>ya?</i>
Why just him?

16:52.637 --> 16:54.514
Why not all his friends
and family?

16:54.514 --> 16:56.766
<i>Ya.</i>
Why not?

16:56.766 --> 16:59.144
He is not only himself.

16:59.144 --> 17:03.022
He is everyone
who cares for him, huh?

17:03.022 --> 17:05.942
Does he have a son or a daughter
who would seek revenge

17:05.942 --> 17:07.652
or a father who works
in the yards

17:07.652 --> 17:09.612
where your ship is repaired

17:09.612 --> 17:11.865
or maybe a lover, huh,

17:11.865 --> 17:14.159
who grows food for your stocks?

17:14.159 --> 17:15.827
Yes, show your strength,

17:15.827 --> 17:18.413
but then show them a smile,

17:18.413 --> 17:20.206
and most will give you
what you want.

17:20.206 --> 17:22.000
Marco knows this.

17:22.000 --> 17:23.626
It's what makes him
so dangerous.

17:23.626 --> 17:25.962
We also dangerous.

17:25.962 --> 17:27.505
[woman]
<i>Oye, bosmang.</i>

17:30.717 --> 17:33.219
It look like they feeding
chromium into the reactor

17:33.219 --> 17:35.388
<i>fo</i> make it seem
more dirty than it is.

17:35.388 --> 17:39.142
Ah, this is Inaros' ship.
I feel it in my bones.

17:39.142 --> 17:40.685
- Have they changed course?
- No.

17:40.685 --> 17:42.896
They maintain deceleration burn.

17:42.896 --> 17:44.773
Still not sure
where they're going.

17:44.773 --> 17:47.317
Yeah, monitor them closely.

17:47.317 --> 17:49.527
And keep us in front
of their drive plume.

17:49.527 --> 17:51.821
<i>Ya, ya.</i>
They <i>na gonya</i> see us coming.

17:52.822 --> 17:55.283
[screen whirs]

17:56.534 --> 17:58.244
Ah, <i>ke.</i>

18:01.456 --> 18:04.751
Okay, Marco, what are you up to?

18:04.751 --> 18:07.921
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

18:07.921 --> 18:14.135
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:14.135 --> 18:15.929
Marco took two rocks,

18:15.929 --> 18:18.139
two chunks of iron.

18:18.139 --> 18:20.391
Ah, he's planning an attack.

18:20.391 --> 18:22.685
Yes, with slag asteroids.

18:22.685 --> 18:24.687
[mutters indistinctly]

18:27.440 --> 18:29.651
Maybe throw them?

18:29.651 --> 18:33.655
Yes, throw them at Tycho
and even Ceres.

18:33.655 --> 18:35.740
Revenge against Fred Johnson
and Anderson Dawes

18:35.740 --> 18:37.784
for what they tried
to do to him,

18:37.784 --> 18:40.119
all with the help of Mars.

18:40.119 --> 18:42.080
How does any of that help Mars?

18:42.080 --> 18:44.582
That's a good question.

18:44.582 --> 18:48.086
Ah, perhaps our Martian
can help us with that.

18:48.086 --> 18:50.755
[choking]

18:50.755 --> 18:52.465
[gurgles]

18:52.465 --> 18:54.259
The dream of Mars isn't dead.

18:54.259 --> 18:56.261
- It's about to be writ large.
[Ashford] Don't do it!

18:56.261 --> 18:59.264
[grunts]

18:59.264 --> 19:00.181
[screams]

19:00.181 --> 19:02.767
[gunshots]

19:05.186 --> 19:06.646
<i>Beratna!</i>

19:06.646 --> 19:09.649
[sobs]

19:11.401 --> 19:17.115
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:17.115 --> 19:20.410
[wind whistling]

19:20.410 --> 19:23.413
[ship whirring]

19:28.042 --> 19:31.045
[medical devices
chirping softly]

19:39.804 --> 19:42.849
I take it
I'm on the <i>Rocinante.</i>

19:44.142 --> 19:46.686
You're not a guest.
You're a prisoner.

19:47.770 --> 19:49.606
Thanks for clearing that up.

20:07.749 --> 20:09.042
Hey.

20:12.837 --> 20:14.255
You okay?

20:17.216 --> 20:20.345
I did all this
to save my family,

20:20.345 --> 20:22.972
and now I'm never going
to see them again.

20:30.647 --> 20:35.276
Well, I'm sure I can talk Holden
into bringing them aboard

20:35.276 --> 20:36.569
so you guys can have a moment.

20:36.569 --> 20:38.321
They will not want to see me.

20:39.781 --> 20:42.200
You got to.

20:42.200 --> 20:43.743
Whatever happens afterwards,

20:43.743 --> 20:45.036
if you don't tell them
how you feel,

20:45.036 --> 20:46.454
you're always gonna regret it.

20:48.706 --> 20:51.459
I waited too long
with my family.

20:51.459 --> 20:54.128
When I was finally ready
to be honest...

20:56.047 --> 20:57.465
...it was too late.

21:01.594 --> 21:04.389
I need to send a report
to Avasarala.

21:05.890 --> 21:07.892
We've been out of contact
for a while.

21:09.978 --> 21:12.480
The Belters
don't have to leave now.

21:12.480 --> 21:13.773
They can borrow
against the ore

21:13.773 --> 21:15.149
and they'll have
relief supplies out there

21:15.149 --> 21:16.985
before we reach Medina.

21:19.487 --> 21:22.490
Are we going to let them stay?

21:22.490 --> 21:24.993
We were never here
to kick anyone out.

21:25.994 --> 21:27.704
Only thing that's changed
is that

21:27.704 --> 21:29.247
all the people
shooting at each other

21:29.247 --> 21:32.208
are either dead
or headed for trial.

21:32.208 --> 21:34.002
Including Lucia.

21:35.294 --> 21:37.922
Whether she intended it or not,

21:37.922 --> 21:40.133
a lot of people died
on that shuttle.

21:40.133 --> 21:42.427
<i>♪ ♪</i>

21:42.427 --> 21:45.513
She didn't mean
for anyone to die,

21:45.513 --> 21:47.932
but they'll still
make an example out of her.

21:49.767 --> 21:52.103
I got the chance
to remake myself,

21:52.103 --> 21:55.106
redeem myself.

21:55.106 --> 21:57.108
Lucia won't get that chance.

21:57.108 --> 22:04.115
<i>♪ ♪</i>

22:05.408 --> 22:07.535
No.
She won't.

22:07.535 --> 22:09.162
And that's a tragedy.

22:10.997 --> 22:13.124
The way she got
thrown out of the <i>Roci</i>

22:13.124 --> 22:15.752
and into space

22:15.752 --> 22:19.672
despite your best efforts
to save her...

22:22.091 --> 22:23.968
...I'll make sure
to note that in my report.

22:23.968 --> 22:26.179
[both chuckle softly]

22:29.057 --> 22:32.143
<i>[Holden] All protomolecule on
Ilus is now completely inert.</i>

22:32.143 --> 22:33.603
<i>And without that trigger,</i>

22:33.603 --> 22:36.606
<i>the alien structures
will remain inert as well.</i>

22:36.606 --> 22:38.149
<i>At the end of the day,
I guess the only</i>

22:38.149 --> 22:40.276
<i>real danger here
was what we brought with us.</i>

22:40.276 --> 22:41.486
[indistinct chatter]

22:41.486 --> 22:43.237
<i>The Belters
and the RCE science team</i>

22:43.237 --> 22:45.156
<i>have decided
to stay on the planet,</i>

22:45.156 --> 22:46.824
<i>working together
to rebuild the settlement</i>

22:46.824 --> 22:49.786
<i>and continue
scientific analysis.</i>

22:49.786 --> 22:51.412
<i>We're coordinating
with the</i> Edward Israel

22:51.412 --> 22:53.331
<i>to take on detainees for trial
as well as move</i>

22:53.331 --> 22:56.542
<i>any additional personnel
and supplies to the surface.</i>

22:56.542 --> 22:58.377
<i>The</i> Roci <i>will escort
the</i> Barbapiccola

22:58.377 --> 23:01.255
<i>back through the Ring so the
Belters can sell their ore.</i>

23:01.255 --> 23:02.381
<i>After what
they've been through,</i>

23:02.381 --> 23:04.008
<i>it's the least we can do.</i>

23:04.008 --> 23:06.260
<i>The</i> Edward Israel <i>will
remain in orbit in support,</i>

23:06.260 --> 23:08.096
<i>parachuting down supplies
as needed</i>

23:08.096 --> 23:09.764
<i>- until relief ships arri...</i>
- [device blips]

23:09.764 --> 23:11.599
Ma'am, this might actually
be good for us.

23:11.599 --> 23:12.809
You were the one who sent Holden

23:12.809 --> 23:14.352
and the <i>Roci</i>
down to New Terra.

23:14.352 --> 23:17.563
Without them,
things could've gone much worse.

23:17.563 --> 23:19.107
The story will be about

23:19.107 --> 23:22.110
how a group of desperate
Belter refugees

23:22.110 --> 23:25.113
and Earth scientists
overcome their prejudices

23:25.113 --> 23:27.990
to stand together
against disaster

23:27.990 --> 23:29.826
on an alien world.

23:29.826 --> 23:32.620
And they made a fortune.

23:32.620 --> 23:35.456
The villains
are dead OPA extremists

23:35.456 --> 23:37.750
and murderous
corporate security,

23:37.750 --> 23:41.295
defeated by the forces of good
for the benefit of all.

23:42.338 --> 23:44.549
Nancy Gao couldn't have
a better narrative

23:44.549 --> 23:47.260
if she had written it herself.

23:47.260 --> 23:50.263
[indistinct chatter]

23:50.263 --> 23:57.270
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:20.168 --> 24:21.043
<i>[woman over P.A. system]
Passengers,</i>

24:21.043 --> 24:22.253
<i>until further notice,</i>

24:22.253 --> 24:23.921
<i>service is suspended
at this station.</i>

24:23.921 --> 24:25.923
<i>We will update you shortly.</i>

24:25.923 --> 24:28.926
<i>[speaking Belter]</i>

24:28.926 --> 24:32.513
<i>[tense music]</i>

24:32.513 --> 24:34.098
[man]
Looks like a cardiac arrest.

24:34.098 --> 24:35.641
Do a tox screen.

24:35.641 --> 24:40.021
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:40.021 --> 24:43.024
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

24:43.024 --> 24:44.275
[keypad chirping]

24:44.275 --> 24:45.568
[line ringing]

24:45.568 --> 24:49.155
[phone trilling]

24:49.155 --> 24:50.573
[device chirps]

24:50.573 --> 24:53.868
<i>♪ ♪</i>

24:53.868 --> 24:55.703
What's up?

24:55.703 --> 24:58.122
Nothing.
Radio silence from here on out.

25:01.334 --> 25:03.044
Fuck.

25:08.174 --> 25:10.760
[Esai] Here's the package.
Where's the money?

25:10.760 --> 25:13.763
[indistinct chatter]

25:18.351 --> 25:20.353
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:20.353 --> 25:22.063
- Esai, it's an ambush!
[man] Shoot her!

25:22.063 --> 25:23.356
[man] Shoot them all!
[Esai] God damn it!

25:23.356 --> 25:24.941
There's no need for this!

25:24.941 --> 25:26.776
-[men shouting]
-[gunshots]

25:26.776 --> 25:28.361
[men yelling]

25:28.361 --> 25:30.154
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:30.154 --> 25:31.572
[grunts]

25:31.572 --> 25:33.366
[gunshots]

25:33.366 --> 25:35.159
[man] Go, go, go!
Elevator open!

25:35.159 --> 25:38.871
[gunfire]

25:38.871 --> 25:43.376
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:43.376 --> 25:45.586
[men shouting]

25:45.586 --> 25:52.593
<i>♪ ♪</i>

25:55.805 --> 25:57.348
What the fuck?

25:57.348 --> 25:59.058
Get out of here!

25:59.058 --> 26:00.476
- Now!
- [whimpers]

26:00.476 --> 26:07.483
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:11.195 --> 26:14.198
[men shouting]

26:14.198 --> 26:21.205
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:22.415 --> 26:24.625
[man]
Left a present for you, bitch!

26:24.625 --> 26:27.628
[device beeping]

26:29.255 --> 26:31.090
[Bobbie] Stop!

26:31.090 --> 26:32.717
[gunshots]

26:32.717 --> 26:36.637
<i>♪ ♪</i>

26:36.637 --> 26:38.597
[device trills and whirs]

26:38.597 --> 26:41.267
Oh, fuck!

26:41.267 --> 26:43.477
[explosion]

26:43.477 --> 26:45.563
[alarms blaring]

26:45.563 --> 26:48.566
[dome rumbling]

27:00.786 --> 27:03.164
[air whooshing]

27:03.164 --> 27:06.000
[electricity crackling]

27:09.045 --> 27:12.048
[alarms blaring]

27:13.966 --> 27:16.552
[debris crashing]

27:16.552 --> 27:19.555
[panting]

27:22.433 --> 27:25.436
[yelping]

27:28.147 --> 27:31.275
[indistinct chatter]

27:31.275 --> 27:34.653
<i>[indistinct announcements
over P.A. system]</i>

27:34.653 --> 27:35.863
[Bobbie]
We're all supposed to be dead.

27:35.863 --> 27:37.073
That was the plan
from the start.

27:37.073 --> 27:38.741
Whose plan?
Not Beltran's.

27:38.741 --> 27:40.910
They killed him too.

27:40.910 --> 27:44.622
<i>[foreboding music]</i>

27:44.622 --> 27:46.624
[Bobbie] There was stealth tech
in those containers.

27:46.624 --> 27:48.959
The Belters must have had help
from someone high up enough

27:48.959 --> 27:51.170
on the food chain to get through
restricted military space.

27:51.170 --> 27:53.255
We need to get off-planet.

27:53.255 --> 27:54.799
I have a cousin on Ceres.

27:54.799 --> 27:56.050
We can go there
until things cool off.

27:56.050 --> 27:57.968
You should go, then.
I've got other plans.

27:57.968 --> 27:59.345
What are you gonna do,

27:59.345 --> 28:02.056
take on the entire
fucking military by yourself?

28:02.056 --> 28:04.016
Not by myself.

28:04.016 --> 28:05.476
Good luck.

28:05.476 --> 28:06.477
Wait.

28:08.020 --> 28:09.772
I'm sorry I got you
into all of this.

28:09.772 --> 28:11.148
Don't be.

28:11.148 --> 28:13.025
At least now
I've got something to do.

28:13.025 --> 28:14.276
[laughs softly]

28:14.276 --> 28:17.279
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

28:17.279 --> 28:24.286
<i>♪ ♪</i>

28:26.914 --> 28:29.917
[wind whistling]

28:37.049 --> 28:39.552
[indistinct chatter]

28:39.552 --> 28:42.221
[tools whirring]

28:42.221 --> 28:45.975
[Carol] This is the last of it.
The Belter camp is all clear.

28:45.975 --> 28:48.853
- Jakob, anything else?
- Just this.

28:48.853 --> 28:50.938
[Elvi] The Belters have started
calling it Second Landing.

28:50.938 --> 28:52.731
Which technically
is not accurate.

28:52.731 --> 28:54.733
They can call it
whatever they want.

28:54.733 --> 28:56.819
It'll work
as a base of operations

28:56.819 --> 28:58.904
until we can set up
a more permanent camp

28:58.904 --> 29:00.448
closer to the artifact.

29:00.448 --> 29:02.867
I think we're gonna
have to add exo-archaeologist

29:02.867 --> 29:04.285
to your résumé.

29:04.285 --> 29:07.371
I want to understand
what really happened,

29:07.371 --> 29:10.249
the war between
those two ancient species.

29:10.249 --> 29:11.834
[Fayez] If there's one thing
geologists are good at doing,

29:11.834 --> 29:13.461
it's digging for answers.

29:13.461 --> 29:14.378
I'll watch her back.

29:17.006 --> 29:20.092
I'm gonna convince the UN

29:20.092 --> 29:22.511
to give you all the resources
you need.

29:22.511 --> 29:25.306
You really believe the artifact
is still a danger to us?

29:25.306 --> 29:27.391
I went inside it.
I'm still here.

29:27.391 --> 29:29.268
<i>[Holden] I think we should
do whatever we can</i>

29:29.268 --> 29:30.519
to make sure
we're not the second

29:30.519 --> 29:33.230
galaxy-spanning civilization
it wipes out.

29:33.230 --> 29:35.024
Galaxy-spanning?

29:35.024 --> 29:36.442
<i>[Holden] We are now.</i>

29:36.442 --> 29:42.156
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:42.156 --> 29:44.200
<i>[Felcia] We'll sell the ore
at Pala Station,</i>

29:44.200 --> 29:45.784
<i>and after that,</i>

29:45.784 --> 29:47.870
I'll move on to a transport
at Tycho Station,

29:47.870 --> 29:50.706
and then it's just
a week over to Ceres.

29:50.706 --> 29:53.000
<i>[Lucia]
I hear Tycho is beautiful.</i>

29:53.000 --> 29:55.920
I'm excited to see it.
I'll be there for a few days.

29:55.920 --> 29:57.796
<i>You be careful now, huh?</i>

29:57.796 --> 29:59.340
<i>Lot of things go on
at a Belter port</i>

29:59.340 --> 30:00.925
<i>that a teenage girl should not
know anything about...</i>

30:00.925 --> 30:02.426
<i>She'll be fine.</i>

30:02.426 --> 30:04.887
<i>She's too smart to mess up
this close to her dream.</i>

30:04.887 --> 30:06.597
Thank you, Mama.

30:06.597 --> 30:09.058
<i>[Jakob] Never forget
that you are in our hearts.</i>

30:09.058 --> 30:12.102
<i>We're always here for you.</i>

30:12.102 --> 30:15.189
Chike, you take care of them.

30:15.189 --> 30:16.774
They're your family now too.

30:16.774 --> 30:18.108
<i>I'll come visit you in space.</i>

30:18.108 --> 30:19.318
<i>[Jakob laughs]</i>

30:19.318 --> 30:21.028
You do that.

30:21.028 --> 30:22.488
All of you.

30:22.488 --> 30:26.283
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:26.283 --> 30:27.743
Good-bye.

30:27.743 --> 30:30.996
<i>[Jakob] Good-bye.
[Lucia] Good-bye. We love you.</i>

30:30.996 --> 30:32.164
[screen blips]

30:32.164 --> 30:39.171
<i>♪ ♪</i>

30:40.714 --> 30:43.300
[Holden] I don't see
anything else down there.

30:45.010 --> 30:46.345
That's all of it.

30:47.304 --> 30:50.558
[Naomi] It'll be nice to get rid
of the protomolecule for good.

31:01.860 --> 31:05.030
Last thing I said to Miller

31:05.030 --> 31:07.866
was that rain
doesn't taste like anything.

31:09.785 --> 31:12.371
Shitty last words to a friend.

31:12.371 --> 31:15.833
What would you say
if you had another chance?

31:19.587 --> 31:22.298
I'd like to know,
if you'd like to share.

31:27.094 --> 31:29.638
I'll go set up
the torpedo flight plan.

31:31.390 --> 31:34.393
Just tell me when you're ready.

31:41.317 --> 31:48.032
<i>♪ ♪</i>

31:48.032 --> 31:49.867
You were right about everything.

31:51.535 --> 31:52.953
You warned us,

31:52.953 --> 31:55.164
but we're charging
through the doors anyway.

31:58.000 --> 32:00.294
If we have any chance
at surviving what comes next,

32:00.294 --> 32:01.920
it'll be because of you.

32:05.466 --> 32:12.473
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:16.435 --> 32:18.062
Rest in peace, brother.

32:20.314 --> 32:23.317
<i>[somber dramatic music]</i>

32:23.317 --> 32:30.324
<i>♪ ♪</i>

32:47.091 --> 32:48.717
Let's give him a minute.

32:51.303 --> 32:53.013
Your hand looks good.

32:53.013 --> 32:55.015
I'm gonna test it out right now.

32:55.015 --> 33:02.022
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:16.078 --> 33:19.081
<i>[foreboding music]</i>

33:19.081 --> 33:21.458
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:21.458 --> 33:23.252
<i>[Naomi] Fred.</i>

33:23.252 --> 33:26.964
A long time ago,
we made a bargain.

33:26.964 --> 33:29.216
I upheld my end.

33:29.216 --> 33:30.843
And now it's your turn.

33:32.386 --> 33:35.264
I need you to help me
find someone.

33:35.264 --> 33:38.684
His name is Filip Inaros.

33:38.684 --> 33:41.270
He's my son.

33:41.270 --> 33:44.773
I have to find him before
his father gets him killed.

33:44.773 --> 33:51.780
<i>♪ ♪</i>

33:53.866 --> 33:55.325
[door whooshes]

34:00.497 --> 34:02.499
The suspense is killing me.

34:11.216 --> 34:14.178
You lost your leg brace.

34:14.178 --> 34:16.555
You all healed up?

34:16.555 --> 34:18.640
Yeah.

34:18.640 --> 34:20.601
Tendons finally finished
growing in.

34:20.601 --> 34:22.978
Why do you care?

34:22.978 --> 34:25.814
I don't wanna beat the shit
out of you if you're gimpy.

34:30.778 --> 34:32.988
We're fighting, are we?

34:34.531 --> 34:37.534
<i>[soft tense music]</i>

34:37.534 --> 34:40.746
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:40.746 --> 34:42.956
You made me kill Wei.

34:42.956 --> 34:43.957
I liked Wei.

34:43.957 --> 34:45.292
[blow lands]

34:45.292 --> 34:48.295
<i>[ominous music]</i>

34:48.295 --> 34:52.216
<i>♪ ♪</i>

34:52.216 --> 34:54.218
Thank you.

34:54.802 --> 34:57.971
<i>[crowd chanting]
Go with Gao! Go with Gao!</i>

34:57.971 --> 34:59.973
<i>[Gao]
Your faith in my vision...</i>

34:59.973 --> 35:02.017
<i>in our shared vision...</i>

35:02.017 --> 35:05.854
<i>is going to change
the arc of our species.</i>

35:05.854 --> 35:08.607
<i>I intend to dedicate
my first term</i>

35:08.607 --> 35:10.776
<i>to fully opening
the Ring Gates</i>

35:10.776 --> 35:14.279
<i>for exploration
and for colonization.</i>

35:14.279 --> 35:16.073
<i>[applause]</i>

35:16.073 --> 35:18.200
<i>And we shall all embrace...</i>

35:18.200 --> 35:20.327
<i>[volume lowering]
...this historic opportunity...</i>

35:20.327 --> 35:22.621
I've been summoned to Luna.

35:22.621 --> 35:24.289
Summoned?

35:24.289 --> 35:26.708
Gao's transition team
has asked me to meet them

35:26.708 --> 35:29.169
at Armstrong Complex.

35:29.169 --> 35:31.171
You could always say no.

35:32.714 --> 35:35.676
That would make me
look ungracious.

35:35.676 --> 35:37.094
And if you go?

35:38.929 --> 35:40.472
Everyone will see

35:40.472 --> 35:42.808
she is setting the agenda.

35:42.808 --> 35:45.269
Never ends.

35:45.269 --> 35:48.063
She won.
She gets to set the agenda.

35:48.063 --> 35:50.524
<i>...has given to us.</i>

35:50.524 --> 35:52.860
Luna might be nice.

35:52.860 --> 35:56.321
We haven't had a vacation
together since...

35:56.321 --> 35:58.156
When did we go to Titan?

36:00.576 --> 36:02.411
You know,
I can't remember either.

36:02.411 --> 36:03.829
[laughs softly]

36:07.040 --> 36:08.917
It might be better if I stayed.

36:08.917 --> 36:10.085
<i>[soft dramatic music]</i>

36:10.085 --> 36:12.504
I have a new semester
to prepare for.

36:12.504 --> 36:14.590
And I think we both
need time to adjust.

36:14.590 --> 36:19.303
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:19.303 --> 36:21.722
- You're angry with me.
[Arjun] No.

36:21.722 --> 36:23.849
I just feel that, um...

36:23.849 --> 36:25.893
Come with me.

36:25.893 --> 36:29.146
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:29.146 --> 36:31.440
Please.

36:31.440 --> 36:34.818
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:34.818 --> 36:36.445
You should go alone.

36:36.445 --> 36:43.452
<i>♪ ♪</i>

36:54.546 --> 36:57.424
<i>[Avasarala] Nancy,
by the time you see this,</i>

36:57.424 --> 37:00.218
<i>you will be Secretary-General.</i>

37:00.218 --> 37:02.054
<i>This will be your chair,</i>

37:02.054 --> 37:05.057
<i>and the system will look
very different from it.</i>

37:05.057 --> 37:08.268
This isn't a job I wanted.

37:08.268 --> 37:10.687
I didn't seek it out.

37:10.687 --> 37:12.397
Once I had it,

37:12.397 --> 37:16.151
it was hard to think
of letting it go.

37:16.151 --> 37:18.946
It won't be easy for you either.

37:18.946 --> 37:21.198
It won't be simple.

37:21.198 --> 37:24.034
And I'll be rooting for you.

37:24.034 --> 37:27.329
If there is anything
I can offer that will help,

37:27.329 --> 37:30.165
any wisdom I can pass on,

37:30.165 --> 37:32.459
it is this.

37:32.459 --> 37:35.504
This chair is not a throne.

37:35.504 --> 37:37.631
We're not queens.

37:37.631 --> 37:40.717
The work we do here is critical,

37:40.717 --> 37:43.136
but it is not all that we are.

37:44.846 --> 37:48.558
Don't forget the rest
of yourself while you do this.

37:50.060 --> 37:52.104
Your time will end too,

37:52.104 --> 37:54.523
and you will want a life
to return to

37:54.523 --> 37:56.274
once this is done.

37:57.484 --> 37:59.361
As for policy

37:59.361 --> 38:01.655
and the direction
you're taking Earth

38:01.655 --> 38:04.449
and all her peoples,

38:04.449 --> 38:08.203
well, we disagree.

38:08.203 --> 38:10.789
One of us is wrong.

38:10.789 --> 38:13.291
I think it's you.

38:13.291 --> 38:16.086
But I hope it's me.

38:16.086 --> 38:17.963
Good luck.

38:17.963 --> 38:20.799
Our future is in your hands now.

38:24.803 --> 38:31.810
<i>♪ ♪</i>

38:48.869 --> 38:50.203
[device blips]

38:55.834 --> 38:57.753
<i>[Bobbie] Ma'am,</i>

38:57.753 --> 38:59.337
<i>I know we didn't leave
on the best terms,</i>

38:59.337 --> 39:02.049
<i>but you're the only one
I can trust to tell.</i>

39:02.049 --> 39:04.760
<i>There's something rotten
on Mars within the military,</i>

39:04.760 --> 39:07.804
<i>some kind of weapons
trafficking with Belters.</i>

39:07.804 --> 39:11.141
<i>I don't know how high up
or what it's for,</i>

39:11.141 --> 39:14.436
<i>not yet,
but it feels dangerous.</i>

39:14.436 --> 39:16.855
<i>Assuming your offer to work
together is still open,</i>

39:16.855 --> 39:18.106
<i>I accept.</i>

39:20.609 --> 39:22.444
<i>I think we need each other.</i>

39:25.614 --> 39:29.284
Bobbie, your timing sucks.

39:31.953 --> 39:34.956
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

39:34.956 --> 39:41.963
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:01.233 --> 40:02.984
[electricity fizzling]

40:02.984 --> 40:05.779
[alarm blaring]

40:05.779 --> 40:07.072
Report?

40:07.072 --> 40:10.242
[man] All scopes blind.
EMP charge scram reactor.

40:11.243 --> 40:13.078
All hands, we are under attack.

40:13.078 --> 40:15.205
Prepare to rebel boarders.

40:15.205 --> 40:20.418
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:20.418 --> 40:23.421
[guns clicking]

40:33.306 --> 40:34.933
[explosion]

40:36.268 --> 40:39.646
[gunshots, glass shattering]

40:39.646 --> 40:46.653
<i>♪ ♪</i>

40:51.908 --> 40:53.827
- [gunfire]
- [grunts]

40:56.329 --> 40:57.581
[grunts softly]

40:57.581 --> 41:00.584
[gunfire]

41:02.627 --> 41:05.297
- [grunting]
- [groans]

41:05.297 --> 41:08.300
[screaming]

41:15.348 --> 41:18.435
[alarm continues blaring]

41:18.435 --> 41:25.066
<i>♪ ♪</i>

41:28.445 --> 41:29.863
[gunshot]

41:29.863 --> 41:32.574
[gunfire]

41:32.574 --> 41:33.825
[grunts]

41:39.706 --> 41:42.083
It's just you and me now, Marco.

41:43.251 --> 41:44.961
[man] Well, not "just."

41:52.135 --> 41:54.638
[Marco] This is Klaes Ashford...

41:55.805 --> 41:57.390
...traitor to the Belt.

42:00.268 --> 42:02.896
This is Filip,

42:02.896 --> 42:04.564
my son.

42:04.564 --> 42:07.400
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:07.400 --> 42:12.447
Nothing you do now
will stop what's coming.

42:17.619 --> 42:20.622
[air lock blares, whooshes]

42:23.917 --> 42:25.752
You're not even
going to try to convince me

42:25.752 --> 42:27.963
to spare your life?

42:27.963 --> 42:32.050
Why would I waste the last few
precious moments I have?

42:32.050 --> 42:34.511
[Marco scoffs]

42:34.511 --> 42:37.264
I'm genuinely going to miss you.

42:37.264 --> 42:39.224
- [device beeps]
[Ashford] You do know, Marco,

42:39.224 --> 42:41.601
that throwing rocks
at Tycho or Ceres

42:41.601 --> 42:43.979
will do little
to harm the Inners.

42:43.979 --> 42:46.064
I agree.

42:46.064 --> 42:48.692
The only real victims there
would be Belters.

42:50.694 --> 42:53.196
Those days are over now.

42:55.115 --> 42:57.534
- [Marco sighs]
- [boot clacks]

43:01.579 --> 43:03.498
You still don't see it.

43:03.498 --> 43:05.542
Eh, don't see what?

43:05.542 --> 43:08.420
[Marco] Can't even imagine it.

43:09.879 --> 43:13.008
This has always been a problem
for our kind.

43:15.677 --> 43:20.056
Even our dreams are small.

43:23.351 --> 43:25.770
Die in darkness,

43:25.770 --> 43:28.106
<i>beratna.</i>

43:30.317 --> 43:32.360
[laughs softly]

43:34.988 --> 43:37.449
- [beep]
- [alarm blares]

43:53.173 --> 43:57.135
<i>♪ To the execution dock ♪</i>

43:57.135 --> 43:59.012
<i>♪ I have come ♪</i>

43:59.012 --> 44:01.890
<i>♪ Tili go ♪</i>

44:01.890 --> 44:04.142
<i>♪ To the execution block ♪</i>

44:04.142 --> 44:06.144
[doors clunking]

44:06.144 --> 44:08.480
<i>♪ For to sail ♪</i>

44:09.981 --> 44:11.566
<i>- ♪ I was sick ♪</i>
- [door whirs]

44:11.566 --> 44:13.860
<i>♪ And nigh to death ♪</i>

44:13.860 --> 44:17.655
<i>♪ But I vow
with my every breath ♪</i>

44:19.157 --> 44:24.746
<i>[voice dwindling]
♪ Fo go with wisdom ways ♪</i>

44:24.746 --> 44:26.748
<i>♪ When I sail ♪♪</i>

44:33.171 --> 44:36.174
<i>[somber violin music]</i>

44:36.174 --> 44:43.181
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:57.153 --> 44:59.489
[device blips]

44:59.489 --> 45:02.325
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

45:02.325 --> 45:05.328
[thrusters whooshing]

45:05.328 --> 45:10.708
<i>♪ ♪</i>

45:10.708 --> 45:12.127
[Marco] Cut thrust.

45:12.127 --> 45:15.130
[indistinct chatter]

45:16.673 --> 45:19.008
Adjust trim
to match target vector.

45:19.008 --> 45:20.427
[woman] All good.

45:23.304 --> 45:25.932
- Release grapples.
[woman] Copy that.

45:25.932 --> 45:30.687
<i>♪ ♪</i>

45:30.687 --> 45:32.605
And launch.

45:35.316 --> 45:38.319
[thrusters whooshing]

45:47.537 --> 45:50.915
What about
their asteroid spotter?

45:50.915 --> 45:52.584
We learned a lot
about their capabilities

45:52.584 --> 45:54.961
from the ship I threw at them,

45:54.961 --> 45:59.174
enough to pick trajectories
to minimize risk of detection.

45:59.174 --> 46:01.968
But even their best instruments
are barely able to penetrate

46:01.968 --> 46:03.970
Martian stealth tech.

46:06.556 --> 46:08.850
The Earthers
will never see them coming.

46:08.850 --> 46:11.895
<i>[ominous music]</i>

46:11.895 --> 46:18.902
<i>♪ ♪</i>
